--misc--
recursive rendering(e.g. import b from B in A.js, then import a from A in B.js):
error = "Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'displayName' of undefined"

Does react Rerender on props change?
A re-render can only be triggered if a component's state has changed. The state can change from a props change, or from a direct setState change. The component gets the updated state and React decides if it should re-render the component.


==redux==
--access store outside react--
https://daveceddia.com/access-redux-store-outside-react/

--misc--
how does redux achieve this: it mapStateToProps, then component props change even after component mounted

--connect--
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/40847699/is-it-possible-to-connect-non-component-class-to-redux-store
The connect function is not going to work with anything other than React components. What you can do is pass your store instance to your class and call store.dispatch, store.getState, and store.subscribe directly.
Keep in mind that if you subscribe, you should also have functionality to unsubscribe, otherwise your store will be holding a reference to your class instance forever, creating a memory leak.

